# ORIG TITLE    French Senate votes to legalise same-sex marriage . 
# ORIG CONTENT  The French Senate has voted to legalise same-sex marriage, which is now on track to become law become by summer. The vote put forward by the Socialists of President Francois Hollande got through despite strong opposition from conservatives, notably Roman Catholics. The bill will permit gay marriage and allow same-sex couples to adopt children. Hollande campaigned for the presidency vowing a change in the law to allow same-sex unions. 
